The paper proposes a method for optimizing neural network architecture through channel pruning, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves using a trainable gate function to optimize loss functions that include discrete values, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of gradient-based training methods, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL).
